description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;East London NHS Foundation Trust in Bedfordshire and Luton has a range of Consultant development opportunities available. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are in a position to tailor Consultant posts according to your interest across our Crisis, Community Mental Health and Inpatient directorates. We are keen to support our Consultants to develop sustainable and stimulating working patterns and we support flexible working arrangements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We offer a generous relocation package and a range of initiatives to support new Consultants joining our organisation. You will access our highly regarded Quality Improvement Science in Action training. We will design a work-plan and training package that can support your academic and leadership development. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For a no-obligation discussion about Consultant opportunities with ELFT in Bedfordshire and Luton, please contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dr Angharad Ruttley - Crisis, Liaison and Perinatal Pathway – &lt;/span&gt;a.ruttley@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dr Guy Thompson – Inpatient Mental Health Services – &lt;/span&gt;guy.thompson@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dr Reena Sani – Community Mental Health Services (Adult and Older Adult) – &lt;/span&gt;reena.sani@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
